{
  "texts": [
    "The energy required to produce SCMs also differs significantly.",
    "SF requires the highest production temperatures, ranging from 1,500 to 2,000°C, while RHA and SCBA are produced at moderate temperatures of 600-700°C.",
    "Correspondingly, CO₂ emissions vary among SCMs.",
    "MK limits 200-400 kg of CO₂ per ton, whereas by-products like FA generate almost no direct emissions.",
    "In summary, low-cost SCMs such as FA are well-suited for sustainable construction projects due to their affordability and environmental benefits."
  ]
}